                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">After soliciting feedback from Clerics, Paladins and Enchanters, along with receiving quite alot of excellent input from everyone. I have done some fine tuning and developed what I believe will be a beneficial spell line. 
<br />

<br />
This line should add significant utility to both Enchanters and Clerics, something that is a new ability, and does not interfere with the abilities of other classes. 
<br />

<br />
Mana costs, casting/recovery/recast times, effect, level limits, and effects have been tuned to scale properly along all levels from beginning to end. 
<br />

<br />
I believe Clerics as the masters of Religion and Enchanters as the masters of mind/philosophy should both receive this line over the entire range. I do not believe that any other classes should have this spell line. Consider it an advanced form of religious and mental control. Other classes lacking the pure faith and mental prowess to use it. 
<br />

<br />
The new premise is: 
<br />
For the first three spell levels, we are questioning a mob, Clerics questioning its religion, its faith, this causes the mob to lose concentration on battle. As we grow in religious power (via levels) we become better at questioning and the spell line power is increased. 
<br />
For the last three spell levels, we have stopped questioning and are now actually challenging the mobs faith. This adds the frenzy radius reduction, as the mob has really lost concentration as we attack its religious nature. 
<br />

<br />
The premise is identical for enchanters however instead of questioning faith they question and challenge philosophy. 
<br />

<br />
The aggro from this spell line should be high, like attack slow and snare. We are really gaining mob focus with this, just like an attack slow or movement slow. 
<br />

<br />
Please review this line. I believe it will be a great boon to add utility to Clerics, and unlike the problems with res and CH, another class will also be able to perform the function from inception. 
<br />

<br />
Seek Beliefs 
<br />
Class: CLR(9) ENC(<img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />
Mana: 50 
<br />
Skill: Alteration 
<br />
Effects: 
<br />
Decrease Casting haste by -2% 
<br />
Target: PC/NPC Targeted 
<br />
Duration: 35 ticks (3 minutes 30 seconds) 
<br />
Casting Time: 3 seconds 500 ms 
<br />
Recovery Time: 5 seconds 
<br />
Recasting Time: 2 seconds 250 ms 
<br />
Resistance Check: Magic +25 
<br />
Range: 200.0 feet 
<br />
Max Level effected: 30 
<br />
Cast on other: %t eyes shine 
<br />
Spell Fades: %t appears alert 
<br />

<br />
Solicit Convictions 
<br />
Class: CLR(24) ENC(24) 
<br />
Mana: 100 
<br />
Skill: Alteration 
<br />
Effects: 
<br />
